    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI have some autocommands to ensure that terminal mode is entered whenever a terminal window is `BufEnter`ed. However, when I switch windows as part of a terminal callback, it seems to not be honored\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate a new file (say `/tmp/bar.vim`) with the following contents:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" File: bar.vim\r\nfunction! s:OnOutput(chan_id, msgs, name)\r\n    let msg = join(a:msgs, '')\r\n    if msg =~ \"foobar\"\r\n        call win_gotoid(s:sourcewin)\r\n        call win_gotoid(s:bashwin)\r\n    endif\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\naugroup EnterTermMode\r\n    au!\r\n    autocmd BufWinEnter,WinEnter term://* startinsert\r\n    autocmd BufWinLeave,WinLeave term://* stopinsert\r\n    autocmd TermOpen * startinsert\r\naugroup END\r\n\r\nlet s:sourcewin = win_getid(winnr())\r\nnew\r\nlet s:bashwin = win_getid(winnr())\r\ncall termopen('bash', { \r\n            \\ 'on_stdout': function('s:OnOutput')\r\n            \\ })\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:so /tmp/bar.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou should fine yourself in the terminal window in terminal mode. To trigger the window commands, type the following in the terminal:\r\n\r\necho \"foobar\"\r\n\r\nNotice that we are no longer in terminal mode even though we got back to the terminal window.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim remains in terminal mode after navigating to the bottom window and back.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.8.0-1210-gd367ed9b2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
